    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0023/1–2947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Benninghoff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Soviet merchant ships are free enter any other than closed ports US without
                    prior arrangement or notification (urtel 19 Jan 29). Soviet naval vessels
                    allowed entry US ports subject prior arrangement. Soviet and other foreign flag
                    vessels not serving occupation may not enter Jap ports without prior permission
                        SCAP.<note n="31" xml:id="d400fn1">Supreme Commander for the Allied Powers,
                        Japan.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
